Rollover

Bonus & Rollover Requirements

We get asked about bonuses and rollover requirements a lot. Here’s what you need to know.

WHAT IS A ROLLOVER REQUIREMENT?

A rollover is an industry-standard wagering requirement that must be met before your funds are available for payout. Most bonuses awarded at MYBookie comes with a rollover requirement attached.

This means that if you claim a bonus, you must rollover (wager) your bonus funds and initial deposit amount a set amount of times before you are eligible for a payout. For Sportsbook bonuses awarded on deposits, typical rollover requirements vary from 3 to 10-times rollover based on your deposit amount.

This means that if your bonus is tagged with a 3-time rollover requirement, you must wager the full amount of your deposit and bonus at least three times before you can request a payout.

ARE ROLLOVER REQUIREMENTS EXCLUSIVE TO MYBOOKIE?

No. Rollover restrictions are a standard requirement attached to all bonuses at online sportsbooks world-wide. MYBookie prides itself in offering its players in offering some of the lowest rollover requirements in the industry.

HOW CAN I AVOID ROLLOVER REQUIREMENTS?

The only way to avoid a significant rollover requirement is to reject a bonus. As per industry-standard, all deposited funds must be wagered at least once prior to requesting a payout.

HOW CAN I FIND OUT MY ROLLOVER REQUIREMENT?

In the cashier, click the info button next to your promocode to see the requirements associated with your deposit bonus. Rollover shown is based on the total combined amount of your deposit and bonus.

I’VE STARTED WAGERING, HOW CAN I TELL MY REMAINING ROLLOVER REQUIREMENT?

Email help@mybookie.cr and we’ll let you know just how close you are to being eligible for your payout.
